is replacing our Roster page - I like the overall look of the Clan MacLear site and having the retired and honory members listed - I do envision GuildMagic enhancing the Roster.  Instead of someone having to keep track of all the current members, when they were promoted, their e-mail address, etc. the person maintaining the roster can get a quick snapshot of what updates need to be made to the Roster.  In addition, the season and time zone of each person is listed which will aid in event planning.  A bonus is that you can list the mastery of your languages and trade skills.  I know I'd prefer to purchase trade skill items from another MacLear before looking to someone else.<br><br>People listed as guild administrators are able to update the seasons and ranks of individuals.  Please register your MacLear characters with GuildMagic <!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://eq.guildmagic.com">eq.guildmagic.com</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--> and I'll send reminders once a month to update the languages/skills.<br><br>Thanks,<br>Lanadena <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccb9b><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub5.ezboard.com/uengelschattenfaust.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Engel Schattenfaust</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC="http://www.duhspot.com/users/smiley/s/games/bof/bof2enemy/csludge.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Kin</span><br>  Posts: 55<br> <font color=#330000>(12/17/01 11:58:21 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub5.ezboard.com/ftheclanmacleargeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1305.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: GuildMagic Request</span><hr size=1> Guildmagic is wonderful. Check out the place where you can do awards and acheivements! Would be fun to have what steps people have reached and then awards for hosting events and participating.. Kind of a history of your character. Makes it easier to know who you could be hunting